### Word order

# 1 SOV Word Order
Source: author
Vetted:
Judgement: g
Phenomena: {Word order, Tense Aspect Mood}
dalla bat kan2wa
dalla bat ka-n2wa
dog.NOM rice.NOM eat-IND
`The dog eats the rice`

# 2 SVO Word Order
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgement: g
Phenomena: {Word order, Tense Aspect Mood}
dalla kan2wa bat
dalla ka-n2wa bat
dog.NOM eat-IND rice.NOM
`The dog eats the rice`

# 3 OSV Word Order
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgement: g
Phenomena: {Word order, Tense Aspect Mood}
bat dalla kan2wa
bat dalla ka-n2wa
rice.NOM dog.NOM eat-IND
`The dog eats the rice`

# 4 OVS Word Order
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgement: g
Phenomena: {Word order, Tense Aspect Mood}
bat kan2wa dalla
bat ka-n2wa dalla
rice.NOM eat-IND dog.NOM
`The dog eats the rice`

# 5 VOS Word Order
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgement: g
Phenomena: {Word order, Tense Aspect Mood}
kan2wa bat dalla
ka-n2wa bat dalla
eat-IND rice.NOM dog.NOM
`The dog eats the rice`

# 6 VSO Word Order
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgement: g
Phenomena: {Word order, Tense Aspect Mood}
kan2wa dalla bat
ka-n2wa dalla bat
eat-IND dog.NOM rice.NOM
`The dog eats the rice`

# 7 AUX following verb
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgement: g
Phenomena: {Tense Aspect Mood}
dalla bat kalaa tiyen2wa
dalla bat ka-laa tiyen2wa
dog.NOM rice.NOM eat-PP has
`The dog has eaten the rice`

# 8 AUX preceding verb
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgement: u
Phenomena: {Tense Aspect Mood}
dalla bat tiyen2wa kalaa
dalla bat tiyen2wa ka-laa
dog.NOM rice.NOM has eat-PP
`The dog has eaten the rice`

### Pronouns

# 1 1pl personal pronoun
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgement: g
Phenomena: {Pronouns, Tense Aspect Mood}
api bat kan2wa
api bat ka-n2wa
We rice.NOM eat-IND
`We eat rice`

# 2 1sg personal pronoun
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgement: g
Phenomena: {Pronouns, Tense Aspect Mood}
mam2 bat kan2wa
mam2 bat ka-n2wa
I rice.NOM eat-IND
`I eat rice`

# 3 3sg personal pronoun
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgement: g
Phenomena: {Pronouns, Tense Aspect Mood}
eyaa bat kan2wa
eyaa bat ka-n2wa
She/he/it rice.NOM eat-IND
`She/he/it eats rice`

# 4 3pl personal pronoun
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgement: g
Phenomena: {Pronouns, Tense Aspect Mood}
eyaala bat kan2wa
eyaa-la bat ka-n2wa
They.3-PL rice.NOM eat-IND
`They eat rice`

# 5 2sg personal pronoun
